1
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Bêlê, her hefte em diçin navçeyekê.
 
Yes, every week we go to a district.

2
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Îro jî em li navçeya Raco ne.
 
Today too we are in the Raco district.

3
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:01,000
Îro jî bernameya me li ser gundê Atmana ye.
 
Today our program is about the village of Atmana.

4
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Em ê biçin ew wextê xweş bi we re derbas bikin,
 
We will go and spend this pleasant time with you,

5
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Hem hemû hevrê derbas, gundê Atmana bibin.
 
We'll take you along with us, to the village of Atmana.

6
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Merheba stêra.
 
Hello stêra.

7
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Welê ehle, merheba. Tû bi xêr hatî.
 
Hello to you too, welcome.

8
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Sax bî. Em destpêkê te nas bikin?
 
Thank you. Let's get to know you first?

9
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Navê min Sebrî ye, Mihemedî Besû ye.
 
My name is Sabri, Mihemedî Besû.

10
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,000
Ser çava Apê Sebrî.
 
You are very welcome, Uncle Sabri.

11
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Em inekî dîroka gundê we j' te pirs dikin. Dîroka gundê
Atmana.
 
We want to ask you a little bit about the history of your
village. The history of the village of Atmana.

12
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Erê... em hewa didin.
 
Yes... we'll tell you.

13
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Inekî em behsa gund bikin. Yanî gund ji çi wexta çêbûye?
 
Let's talk a bit about the village. That is, from what time
was the village built?

14
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Berî gund li vir bû an li cîkî din bû?
 
Was the village here before or in another place?

15
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Welle gund... ewa li meşê bûye.
 
Well the village... it was in the oak forest.

16
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Da berê jî xwedan pez bûn, der bûn.
 
In the past they were sheep owners, they were outside.

17
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Vêra dibêjin Gola Xirbê. Li wê derê konên reş hebûn, der
hebûn.
 
They call it Gola Xirbê. There were black tents there, they
were outside.

18
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Li wêra jî malbatê Dûrê jî, meriyên xwe hebûn.
 
And there, the Dûrê family, they had their people.

19
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,000
De kî bûn, em nizanin.
 
And who they were, we don't know.

20
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:26,000
Ta bîn ne malik bi tenê ye, malbatê Dûrê hebûn.
 
Not just one family, there was the Dûrê family.

21
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Qîzek malê dwiye Reş xwestin.
 
The Reş family asked for a girl from the other family.

22
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Malbatê Reş jî li Dureşo bû.
 
The Reş family was in Dureşo.

23
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:33,000
Wî jî qîza xwe dayê.
 
He also gave his daughter.

24
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Ba'dî wextêkî şûnda, qîz çû zeyî, mala bavê kê.
 
After a while, the girl went to visit, to her father's
house.

25
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Ap kê teme kir...
 
Her uncle advised her...

26
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Got: "Em xanî li vir in." Ji bo mêrê xwe, gundê mêrê xwe.
 
He said: "We have a house here." To her husband, the village
of her husband.

27
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:48,000
"Tineye tiştek... şûnê gund bi me de."
 
"There is nothing... leave the place of the village to us."

28
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,000
"Şûnê em li wê derê bihewirin."
 
"So that we can settle there."

29
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:56,000
Hanî Dwiye Reş wê derê dayê. Vê malbatên Dûrê...
 
Thus Dwiye Reş gave them that place. This Dûrê family...

30
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:02,000
Etmîn yanî Etmîn bavê duwî kê, gî kî vêra bû? Sê gav vêra
hatin.
 
Etmin, I mean Etmin the father of the second one, who was
here? They came here in three steps.

31
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Li wê derê şên kirin û giştî jî li vî gundî halhazir gî
hene.
 
They built it up there and generally all of them are
currently in this village.

32
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Yanî tu wek hewa didî, berî gund ne li vir bû, piştî wê
derbasî vir bû?
 
So as you say, before the village wasn't here, it moved here
after that?

33
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:15,000
Yanî navê gund jî ji yek kesî hatiye? Navê wî Etman bûye
yanî?
 
So the name of the village also comes from one person? His
name was Etman?

34
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Navê bapîrê... malê duwî kê, Etman bû.
 
The name of the grandfather... of the second family, was
Etman.

35
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:24,000
Mala Bilê Ûsiv... da digotin Bilê Ûsiv. Hew jî hew bû, hew
jî nakok li Atmana ye.
 
The Bilê Ûsiv family... they used to say Bilê Ûsiv. He was
him, he is also currently in Atmana.

36
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:27,000
E berê li gund, çi derê bû yanî?
 
And where was the village before?

37
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Li vir na gund bûn... na... Li kû derê bû?
 
Here there were no villages... no... Where was it?

38
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Eşte li Raskav, navê wêra dibêjin, ma ser heye,
 
Like at Raskav, that's what they call it, maybe it is up
there,

39
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:36,000
Gola Xirbê heye, Curnê Etmîn heye.
 
There's Gola Xirbê, there's Curnê Etmîn.

40
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Da xwedan pez bûn.
 
They were sheep owners.

41
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,000
Xweş. Ber bi jêr e?
 
Good. Towards the lower part?

42
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,000
Ser du kîlometre heye.
 
It's about two kilometers away.

43
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:42,000
Di nav çiyê de ye?
 
Is it in the mountain?

44
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Erê di çiyê de ye.
 
Yes, it is in the mountain.

45
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:49,000
Û eşte paşê... gî berê xwe hatin vê gundê şên kirin.
 
And then after... they all came towards here and built this
village.

46
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:55,000
Naka jî dîmekî malbatê, mala dwiye kê ye, mala Bilê Ûsiv e,
mala Hemîd Fat Reş kê ye.
 
Now also some of the family, the family of the second one,
Bilê Ûsiv's family, Hemîd Fat Reş's family.

47
00:04:55,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Mala Şêx Zeyn e lê. Mala Mihemedî Nehs kê ye, mala Reşîdê
Berîfat kê ye... Hîn malên meşî yên merî kê jî hebûn.
 
The family of Şêx Zeyn. The family of Mihemedî Nehs, the
family of Reşîdê Berîfat... There were still shepherd
families of his relatives.

48
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Havna li vir in. Didiwê wê ro malik, Mihemedî Bêtil jî.
 
These are here. Second to that day a family, Mihemedî Bêtil
too.

49
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:12,000
Li havî hebî hew jî penç şeş sal heye, hew jî li vir e.
 
If there's anyone, he's also been here for five or six
years.

50
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:17,000
Gundî me naka şên e, ha vana jî bi jina, dera gî qir bûn e,
mirî hene.
 
Our village is populated now, these guys too with wives,
outsiders were completely destroyed, there are dead ones.

51
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,000
Û giş xaxane.
 
And they are all landowners.

52
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,000
Çiqas xanî di gundî we de hene?
 
How many houses are there in your village?

53
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Xanî 200 malî heye naka.
 
There are 200 households right now.

54
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:28,000
Û hîn jî kombûn, ser 70 heqasî, dizî hatin li der va heye.
 
And they also gathered, about 70 of them, illegally came
outside.

55
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,000
Li kî derê ne?
 
Where are they?

56
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,000
Li Helebê ne, li Efrînê ne...
 
In Aleppo, in Afrin...

57
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:34,000
Li Şamê hene.
 
There are some in Damascus.

58
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Qismin, çûne yê alî Tirkiyê, milkê xwe berê vir gî yek bû.
 
A part of them, they went to the side of Turkey, their
property was previously all one here.

59
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Wêr jî Sûriyê yanî... milkê vir û Tirkiyê gî bi hev de, bi
rê bû.
 
There is also Syria... the property here and Turkey were all
together, it was on the road.

60
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,000
Xudût, midût tinebû.
 
There were no borders at all.

61
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:49,000
Qismek jî naka li wêr jî mayî. Milk li wêr e.
 
A part of them also stayed there now. The property is there.

62
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:51,000
Li navçeya Raco rûniştin e?
 
Are they residing in the Raco district?

63
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Raco jî rûniştin e, erê, li gundera rûniştin e.
 
Residing in Raco too, yes, residing in the villages.

64
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Atmana li giş dera ne. Her e li wêrî ne.
 
Atmanans are everywhere. Yes they are there.

65
00:05:56,000 --> 00:06:00,000
Ke em herin cem apê jî û çend pirsa ji apê dipirsim.
 
Let's go to the uncle as well and ask a few questions to the
uncle.

66
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,000
Merheba stêra jî.
 
Hello to you too, stêra.

67
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:04,000
Merheba, ehlen we sehlen, hûn bi xêr û selamet axa welat.
 
Hello, welcome, you came with goodness and peace to the land
of the homeland.

68
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:07,000
Sax bî, apê em te jî nas bikin?
 
Thank you, uncle, let's get to know you too?

69
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Ezedîn Qerehso.
 
Ezedîn Qerehso.

70
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,000
Ser çava Apê Ezedîn.
 
You are very welcome, Uncle Ezedîn.

71
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:15,000
Behsê gundekî din kir, ew jî li ser xetê ye, yanî li milî
Tirkiyê, milî Bakurê Kurdistanê ye.
 
He talked about another village, that is also on the border,
meaning on the Turkish side, the Northern Kurdistan side.

72
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,000
Navê wî gundî çiye?
 
What is the name of that village?

73
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:20,000
Navê wî qe... li wêr vê ra dibêjin Qereqiç, lê wisa ez
nizanim.
 
Its name is qe... there they call it Qereqiç, but like that
I don't know.

74
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Yanî ew jî eynî ji malbatên we ne?
 
So they are also from your families?

75
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:26,000
Giş ji vê gundî ne, ji gundî me ne.
 
They are all from this village, from our village.

76
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:29,000
E ku çawa demê da li şûna wira? Li demê berê da li wêr bûn?
 
So how did they settle there at that time? Were they there
in the past?

77
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,000
Berê sînor da ket.
 
Before, it fell within the border.

78
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,000
Sînor da ket...
 
It fell within the border...

79
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:36,000
Xetê... piştî tirkî îstîlo îhtîlal kir.
 
The line... after Turkey invaded, occupied.

80
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,000
Sala 38'a.
 
In the year '38.

81
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:40,000
Ew li navçeya Qirixanê ne?
 
Are they in the Qirixan district?

82
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Qirixanê... nêzîkê Qirixanê ne... nêzîk gundê Încirlî yê.
 
Qirixan... near Qirixan... near the village of Incirli.

83
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:47,000
Serê Kaniyê, Gira Resûl.
 
Serê Kaniyê, Gira Resûl.

84
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,000
Her ew gundê nêzîkê ne yanî?
 
Those are the nearby villages, right?

85
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,000
E te dî Qereqic... e tê dî... cem yan a qûze.
 
Yes, you see Qereqic... you see... at the northern side.

86
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:54,000
E ma têkiliyek navbera we da heye? Hûn diçin tên?
 
So is there any relationship between you? Do you visit each
other?

87
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Nê... derê... na. Eşte car car munasabe hebin tên.
 
No... way... no. Except sometimes if there are occasions,
they come.

88
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,000
Ser sînor.
 
At the border.

89
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:03,000
Aramî be... derê... nê... Sînor a. Çi kî mixatere bê... nare
netê.
 
If there is peace... out there... no... The border is.
Whatever risk there might be... doesn't go, doesn't come.

90
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:06,000
E ku çan kevn e, gundê we kevn e, li vî gundî?
 
So since when is it old, your village is old, in this
village?

91
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Na, gundê me yê kevn e.
 
No, our village is the old one.

92
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,000
Yanî ji vir çûne wê ra?
 
So they went from here to there?

93
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,000
Ji vir çûne wê ra.
 
They went from here to there.

94
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:11,000
Berê ev erda we bûn yanî?
 
These lands were yours in the past, right?

95
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:15,000
Erê erê, erd erdê ev gundiya bûn, erê.
 
Yes, yes, the land, the lands were of these villagers, yes.

96
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:17,000
Ê wilo bîn.
 
Yes, they were like that.

97
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:22,000
Na em behsa ewî bikin, berê gundê we rûspiyê we kî bûn? Di
vî gundî da rûspiyê we kî bûn?
 
Now let's talk about that, who were the elders of your
village in the past? Who were your elders in this village?

98
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:27,000
Ê tedbîrê, mezin... ê xart Mehdî bûn, wî demê çi wekî bûn,
Mehdî bû ta tarê dwiwê kê, wê ra digotin.
 
The ones with measures, elders... old Mahdi was, whatever
they were at that time, Mahdi was until the date of the
second one, they called him that.

99
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,000
Me ha wû dît bû.
 
We had seen him like that.

100
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:31,000
De dwiwê rojî vanî hûrik mûrik eşta divê me derketa...
 
Since the second day of these small things we had to come
out...

101
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Muxatrê gundî me hebûn, yanî Hesenê Elî, Silêmanê Bilî...
 
Our village had headmen, meaning Hesenê Elî, Silêmanê
Bilî...

102
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:39,000
Mihemedê Na'sê. Eşte wan ê ya ne... Liva rê ew dikirin.
 
Mihemedê Na'sê. Except those were... They did the leading.

103
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Ya ne çend rûspî hebûn.
 
That is, there were a few elders.

104
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
De gî pismamê hev in lo, gî meriyên hev in ha.
 
They are all cousins, you see, they are all relatives to
each other.

105
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:46,000
Berê gund zatî giştî mirovê hev in, gî meriyên hev in.
 
In the past, the village was essentially all people of each
other, all relatives of each other.

106
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:50,000
Gî gî, jina dayî wergirtiye, di nav giştî de bê aşna bûn, bi
nav meriyên hev bûn.
 
All, all, gave women, received, among all they were
acquainted, among relatives of each other.

107
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,000
Apê Ezedîn ez dikarim xwestek tiştekî te pirs kim?
 
Uncle Ezedîn, can I ask you one thing?

108
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:56,000
Cem we dibêjin Erdê Kevir, Erdê Kolkê.
 
In your area they say Land of Stone, Land of Kolk.

109
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,000
Ew çi maneyê dide?
 
What does that mean?

110
00:07:57,000 --> 00:08:00,000
De wekî em dibêjin de em nizanin ma bela xêr rast e...
 
As we say, we don't know if by chance it's true...

111
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,000
E nizanin.
 
I don't know.

112
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:06,000
Koprîk a. Koprîk a, ha şor e em dibêjin. Hera dere...
 
It is Koprîk. Koprîk, that is the talk we say. Goes there...

113
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:10,000
Berê te bi kopriyek dînî? O wê reş a em dibêjin erda ketî.
 
In the past you see a bridge? That black one we say fell on
the land.

114
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:13,000
Ê erdê Edem o. Ard na sere li vî gundî.
 
It is the land of Adem. Earth is not dominant in this
village.

115
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,000
Gundî kê heye, navê wî Adem o.
 
There is a villager, his name is Adem.

116
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:19,000
Wano rabûyî go gundî me yê... Etmana go ê me yê... temet
nav...
 
Those ones rose up said it is our village... Atmana said it
is ours... exact name...

117
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,000
Nêzîkê hav din e...
 
It's close to each other...

118
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,000
Cimaet kombûn mehkeme tinebû,
 
People gathered, there was no court,

119
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:26,000
Go xayî... rûspî ketin mobêna go em î îşî çêkin.
 
He said, brothers... elders intervened, said we will fix
this matter.

120
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:30,000
Du mêra şandin... yek şandin li vî gundî, yek şandin Adem
o...
 
They sent two men... sent one to this village, sent one to
Adem o...

121
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:36,000
Ê Ademo wa li mêrk o, yanî şîv axo, fêkî... germî... çî
heye, em nizanin,
 
The Ademo one fed the man, I mean fed him dinner, fruit...
soup... whatever there is, we don't know,

122
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:37,000
Gûştî dînî ser...
 
Gave him meat on top...

123
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:44,000
Ci mêrê tir... vi derê... ca mêrtir der ketin... hotin, ê li
dera çi kirin? Kulîk kirin...
 
From the other man... this place... stronger man came out...
came, what did they do outside? Made kulîk (bread/food)...

124
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:50,000
Berdan satil ê.. nê, qapox jî da ne ser, geş da hîn... îşta
ki porê we xistin... germî...
 
Dropped it in a bucket.. no, put a lid on it too, prospered
yet... whatever hair they put in it... soup...

125
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Xwariye û go de hema bera...
 
He ate and said well just let it...

126
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:55,000
Çû me... ser kê şa we da dî wê?
 
We went... to whom did they give it?

127
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Mehkeme wa kî bûn ev rûspî?
 
Who were these elders in the court?

128
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:05,000
Go bixwê me em rûnin, wile ew xwarina germ xwar û xwêdan da
û ewî qet nedîtin, ard çend kî bûn wê bi... wî da ard dayê
te gundê Adem o. Go ev erda de ye.
 
Said let's sit ourselves, by God he ate that hot food and
sweated and didn't see anything, lands were several that
were... he gave the land to you, village of Adem o. Said
this land is yours.

129
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:08,000
Yanî gotin ev kê xwarina germ anî... ewî erdê dibe?
 
You mean they said whoever brought the hot food... he takes
the land?

130
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:09,000
E rî...
 
Ye s...

131
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,000
Heta naka jî dibêjin erdê we...
 
Even now they say your land...

132
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:13,000
Dibêjin erdê me ne, erd ard me. Çu erda çûye...
 
They say our lands, the land is our land. But the land is
gone...

133
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,000
Yanî navê erdê ew jûr hatiye?
 
So the name of the land came from above?

134
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:21,000
Jûr hatî jî, edam a hatî... De wê da... ew erd e ber... ev
zeviya wê ber...
 
It came from above, also adama came... From there... that
land is below... this field is below...

135
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,000
Na em behsa çandiniyê bikin.
 
Now let's talk about agriculture.

136
