476
00:45:01,000 --> 00:45:06,000
Navê Textê Mîr ha ev e, gorî ez zanim se...
 
The name, Textê Mîr... well, as far as I know...

477
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:12,000
Ekîd mîr li wî derî bûye. Wana jî di nav kevira daye.
 
Surely a mir was there. They also put it among the stones.

478
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:19,000
Bes feqet fere ye, ev bi vî rengî dibêjin Textê Mîr. Ew nav
ji vir hatiye.
 
But it's wide, so they call it the Textê Mîr. That name
comes from here.

479
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:23,000
Hema tu li çiyê bibînî, ser ta binî...
 
Whenever you look at the mountain, from top to bottom...

480
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:28,000
Xirabe ne, lê pirr in. Dîware ne, xirabe ne.
 
They are ruins, but there are many. There are walls, ruins.

481
00:45:28,000 --> 00:45:35,000
Gorî tarîxê dibêjin, ji berî vê, bi sê mîlyon sal e
teqrîben...
 
According to history, they say, about three million years
ago approximately...

482
00:45:35,000 --> 00:45:40,000
Ji berî vê bi sê mîlyon sal e teqrîben wî derê şên bûye, ev
çiya tijî bûne.
 
About three million years ago approximately, this area was
populated, these mountains were full.

483
00:45:40,000 --> 00:45:43,000
Di nexş û îşaretek lê hene?
 
Are there any patterns and signs on it?

484
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:49,000
Weleh îşaret wane em dibînin lê hene. Me nedîtine. Feqet
dîwar hene.
 
Well, we see those signs on it. We haven't seen them
[clearly]. But there are walls.

485
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:50,000
Hene?
 
Are there?

486
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:53,000
Dîwar hatine ko lê hene.
 
The walls remain, they are there.

487
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:55,000
Emê mala te ava be...
 
Bless you...

488
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:56,000
Sax be.
 
Thank you.

489
00:45:56,000 --> 00:45:58,000
Ka tu naha, kîjan tişt ji me re ser vê çiyê... Hîn çi di vî
çiyayî de heye?
 
So now, what can you tell us about this mountain... What
else is there in this mountain?

490
00:45:58,000 --> 00:46:00,000
Hebe çal in.
 
There are pits.

491
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:04,000
Berê çal in... Berê dûr bûn ji gundî, gundiyan kirin
sarinc...
 
There are pits... They were far from the village, the
villagers made them into cisterns...

492
00:46:04,000 --> 00:46:08,000
Di bin re dibêjin rêsale zeytûn hene. Darê zeytûnê hene.
 
Below, they say there are olive roots. There are olive
trees.

493
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:12,000
Serî şikeft e. Şikeft li pêş heye...
 
At the top is a cave. There's a cave in front...

494
00:46:12,000 --> 00:46:13,000
Navê wê şikeftê çî ye?
 
What is the name of that cave?

495
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:19,000
Navê wê... nizanin dibêjin Serê Şikeftê.
 
Its name... they don't know, they say Top of the Cave.

496
00:46:19,000 --> 00:46:22,000
Û pirr e, evê wekî gir der dibêjin...
 
And there are many, like they say about the hill...

497
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:24,000
Çi, wek gihandina zeytûnê...
 
Like olive processing...

498
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:28,000
Li serî Hêrik. Cihê me'serê, niha xwe eciqandinê.
 
Above Hêrik. A place for the press, to press it.

499
00:46:28,000 --> 00:46:31,000
Naha di behsa çalan dikir, çend çal li vir hene?
 
Now regarding the pits you mentioned, how many are here?

500
00:46:31,000 --> 00:46:33,000
Weleh, dudu-sêyek hebûn...
 
Well, there were two or three...

501
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:37,000
Bes ew gat xitimandin. Ev e, niha ev kirin sarinc. Ev sarinc
e.
 
But they got blocked. Now they made this a cistern. This is
a cistern.

502
00:46:37,000 --> 00:46:41,000
Tu zani, naha ew çal jî, ma we bo çi, ji bo çi hatine
çêkirin bo? Te wextekî dît?
 
Do you know what those pits were built for? Did you see it
at the time?

503
00:46:41,000 --> 00:46:50,000
Weleh, ji bo meyê. Bes kûr bûn... wexta, dibêjin wî çaxê
genimê xwe dikirin... zexîreyê xwe tiştê xwe dikirinê. Tê de
hiltanîn.
 
Well, for wine maybe. But they were deep... they say at that
time, they used to store their wheat, their provisions,
their stuff there. They kept it inside.

504
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:57,000
Osmaniyan li, berî osmaniya ev li vir bûye, evê wekî çete
hebûye, der bûn, li vir ewan wisa dikir, belê...
 
The Ottomans, before the Ottomans this was here, there were
like bandits, they were outside, they used to do that here,
yes...

505
00:46:57,000 --> 00:46:59,000
Yanî berî her malekê çal û qulek...
 
So before every house [there was] a pit or a hole...

506
00:46:59,000 --> 00:47:02,000
Ekîd, hebû, mala paş me dîsa çal û reke hebû kirine sarinc.
 
Surely, there were. Behind our house there was a pit and a
crack, they made it a cistern.

507
00:47:02,000 --> 00:47:04,000
Ji bo zexîreya xwe tê de dikirin, veşartin...
 
To store their provisions inside, hide them...

508
00:47:04,000 --> 00:47:07,000
Ji bo zexîreya xwe tê de dikirin, ev e di kûr de ev e.
 
To put their provisions inside, it's deep inside.

509
00:47:07,000 --> 00:47:09,000
Û kî ye, ev qul a kê ye?
 
And whose, whose hole is this?

510
00:47:09,000 --> 00:47:15,000
Ev a... ev ê dibêjin Mehmed Elî... Ewe ew pismamê me ye. Û
qul e fetişîne li wira. Ev qul li dera...
 
This... this is said to belong to Mehmed Elî... He's our
cousin. And they search around there. This hole out here...

511
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:17,000
Dayê ev wekî qul e?
 
Mother, is this like a hole?

512
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:18,000
Ne qul e yabo.
 
It's not a hole, my child.

513
00:47:18,000 --> 00:47:19,000
Hê?
 
Huh?

514
00:47:19,000 --> 00:47:20,000
Erê bilê.
 
Yes, exactly.

515
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:22,000
Ev wekî bîr e, yan sarinc e va?
 
Is this like a well or a cistern?

516
00:47:22,000 --> 00:47:27,000
Ev sarinc e. Sûv, pêş te, û çil tûrên çîmento min lê xist.
 
This is a cistern. Sand, [unknown], and forty bags of cement
I put in it.

517
00:47:27,000 --> 00:47:35,000
Min xatên lê xistin. Kalê min kete çav. Min bi xwe ser
çestîk rakir. Daxê qulî yî.
 
I put lines in it. My grandfather fell in. I got up with my
own hands. The mark of the hole.

518
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:40,000
Ne kîs çê bi çestîk. Git tev qul e. Helalî gewre ye ev.
 
Not a bag [unknown], this is entirely a hole. It's truly
huge.

519
00:47:40,000 --> 00:47:47,000
Û kort, çal, fenekî ye wekî bî waz li ser erdê bû. Îşaret
hebî, teslîm ker, vê ket.
 
And a depression, a pit, it was open to the surface. It had
marks, surrender, fall into it.

520
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:51,000
Qul e bitenê, ne canek heye, ne leqem, ne tiştek...
 
Just a hole, with no life inside, no depth, nothing...

521
00:47:51,000 --> 00:48:00,000
Û lawekî me ew dîn ew xort e sêfîre. Cûcik bû, deh salî bû,
min tê da reşke dida. Û...
 
And there, that crazy boy is squeezing... He was small, ten
years old, I used to give him a little water. And...

522
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:07,000
Hema me kiribû yê, ax jê dikişandin. Heta çil zembîl e, ya
te ba ne hesibîne.
 
We got angry, digging the soil. Up to forty baskets, from
yours they don't count...

523
00:48:07,000 --> 00:48:12,000
Çil zembîl min ji binî derxistin. Û paşê av da ketiye. De ev
e.
 
Forty baskets I took out from the bottom. And then water
filled it. That's it.

524
00:48:12,000 --> 00:48:15,000
De çend sal... Beriya vê bi çend salan ev bû?
 
How many years... How many years ago was this?

525
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:24,000
Ev a? Weleh... ewanî weha mezin nebûn. Emrê min heftê ye...
Emrê min heftê û dudu ye.
 
This? Well... the water wasn't that big. I'm seventy... I'm
seventy-two.

526
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:26,000
De tu çend salî bûyî wê demê?
 
So how old were you at that time?

527
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:30,000
Ez heştdeh salî bûm. Dema ew hate çêkirin da min camî de
vala kir. Heştdeh salî bûm.
 
I was eighteen... When it was built I emptied the glass. I
was eighteen...

528
00:48:30,000 --> 00:48:31,000
Tu ji kîjan gundî yî?
 
Which village are you from?

529
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:32,000
Ez ji gundê Qadê me.
 
I am from the village of Qadê.

530
00:48:32,000 --> 00:48:33,000
Tu bûka vî gundî yî?
 
You are a bride of this village?

531
00:48:33,000 --> 00:48:35,000
Ez bûka vî gundî me.
 
I am a bride of this village.

532
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:37,000
Dema tu hatî te ev sarinca vekir?
 
When you came, you opened this cistern?

533
00:48:37,000 --> 00:48:40,000
Erê, hatim me min girt, sarinc vekir.
 
Yes, I came and opened the closed cistern...

534
00:48:40,000 --> 00:48:41,000
Çend rojan berxwe da?
 
How many days did it take?

535
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:42,000
Ço?
 
What?

536
00:48:42,000 --> 00:48:43,000
Çend rojan de we xilas kir?
 
In how many days did you finish it?

537
00:48:43,000 --> 00:48:47,000
Weleh mehok e. Xwedî de rûnim... bi tenê canê xwe bûm ha.
 
Well, it was a month. I swear... I was working all by
myself.

538
00:48:47,000 --> 00:48:50,000
Yanî, destpêkê te xwe da nav qulê nîv e, wek xaniyekî we
vekir, te av da?
 
So, initially you went into the hole half-way, you opened it
like a house, you gave it water?

539
00:48:50,000 --> 00:49:03,000
Min dît vir wek erdê ye. Heta min keviran şikand, da. Min
dît wek erdek e, na na me şikand, lawikê me sefîr hat, qulp
tê da.
 
I saw it like the ground, until we broke the stones. We made
a house like the ground, no no, we broke it, our boy stood
up, put the clay.

540
00:49:03,000 --> 00:49:08,000
Hat, qev da, ev e... qevra xwe dî kir.
 
The dirt... it came... its own dirt and stones were seen.

541
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:09,000
Niha av tê de heye?
 
Is there water in it now?

542
00:49:09,000 --> 00:49:17,000
Heye. Ava wê, we dî, tê de ye. Ava baranê ye. Ê baranê ye ev
e.
 
There is. The water... we look, it's there. From the rain...
The rain. This is it.

543
00:49:17,000 --> 00:49:21,000
De ev e, ko li mikra kar hat e. De ava baranê heta derva
dihat...
 
This is it, it became useful. The rainwater used to come
out...

544
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:26,000
Bi zehmetî, rê şikeft e. Me got me xilas kir.
 
With effort... It's the path of the cave. We said we
finished it.

545
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:32,000
Sed û nod mêtre heta xertîme, qirp in arde ne ra ye.
 
About a hundred and ninety meters until it gets full, it's
flat on the ground.

546
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:34,000
Spasiya te dikim dayê.
 
Thank you, mother.

547
00:49:34,000 --> 00:49:36,000
Ê ger tiştekî din hebe tu dixwazî mer bêje.
 
If there's anything else you want to say.

548
00:49:36,000 --> 00:49:38,000
(muffled)
 
(muffled)

549
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:44,000
Saeta we xweş. Ob xêr hatin we dikin. Û gelek spas.
 
May your time be pleasant. You are welcome. And thank you
very much.

550
00:49:44,000 --> 00:49:46,000
Axa welat...
 
The homeland's soil...

551
00:49:46,000 --> 00:50:06,000
Yanî ev mecalek da vî gundî. Firsendek daye, hatin vir
muqabelek çêkirin. Û saeta we xweş.
 
I mean, they gave an opportunity to this village. Gave an
opportunity, came here, made an interview. And have a good
time.

552
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:11,000
Belê, îro jê em hevrê gundekî din nas kir.
 
Yes, today we got to know another village together.

553
00:50:11,000 --> 00:50:15,000
Me gundê Etmana nas kir. Inik, taybetmendiya vî gundî,
 
We got to know the village of Etman. Currently, the
characteristic of this village,

554
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:18,000
inik dîroka vî gundî.
 
currently the history of this village.

555
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:32,000
Li vir jî em gihîştin dawiya bernameya xwe. Heya hefteyek
din we emanetî nav xêr û xweşiyê dikim, bi xatirê we.
 
Here too we have reached the end of our program. Until next
week, I entrust you to goodness and happiness, goodbye.

556
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:38,000
Îlahî te erşêk çêkir
 
O God, you built a throne

557
00:50:38,000 --> 00:50:48,000
Allah bi ser ser ye
 
Allah is above all heads

558
00:50:48,000 --> 00:50:56,000
Teyrekî mexfî ye cismê min, qaneta per ye
 
My body is a hidden bird, its wings are feathers

559
00:50:56,000 --> 00:51:04,000
Te nûr xelq kir Allah, Allah bi ser ser ye
 
You created light, O Allah, Allah is above all heads

560
00:51:04,000 --> 00:51:11,000
Te navê lê na bi cût, yek şems yek qemer ye
 
You named them in pairs, one is the sun, one is the moon

561
00:51:11,000 --> 00:51:18,000
Li rûyê semawe sewa, kir cî û fener ye
 
On the face of the sky alike, made a place and lantern

562
00:51:18,000 --> 00:51:26,000
Bona xatirê Nebî Muhemmed, Gulê Pêxember e
 
For the sake of Prophet Muhammad, the Rose of Prophets

563
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:33,000
Eman eman eman, sed carî nezer darî
 
Aman, aman, aman, a hundred times looking at the face

564
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:40,000
Bi navê silsiley Seyda ra, himet bîn hevalî
 
In the name of the chain of Seyda, let the effort be a
companion

565
00:51:40,000 --> 00:51:48,000
Bi navê pêxember Muhemmed ra, sadiq dost û yar e
 
In the name of Prophet Muhammad, a true friend and companion

566
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:54,000
Daxil ek ya Rifa'î ye, bende derban ye
 
I seek your refuge, O Rifa'i, servant of the doors

567
00:51:54,000 --> 00:52:01,000
Elmeded ya Evdilqadir, bazê Geylan e
 
Help, O Abd al-Qadir, the falcon of Gilan

568
00:52:01,000 --> 00:52:08,000
Elmeded ya Bedawî, sahibul burcan e
 
Help, O Bedawi, owner of the towers

569
00:52:08,000 --> 00:52:16,000
Elmeded ya Disûqî, şêxê şêxan e
 
Help, O Disuqi, sheikh of sheikhs

570
00:52:16,000 --> 00:52:21,000
Elmeded kamil pîr e, bavê mirşîdan e
 
Help, perfect old man, father of guides

